<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A little known species, apparently endemic to Guerrero State in Mexico.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Guerrero</emphasis>
: Casa Verde, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. Kruse</emphasis>
s.n. [14/2/1970] (MEXU); Eduardo Neri, Venta Vieja, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. A. Aguilar</emphasis>
34 (MEXU); Zopilote canyon, Chilpancingo -
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Balsas, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. Mostul</emphasis>
1161A (OXF).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The large, nearly white, sericeous corolla, the subequal sericeous sepals and the included anthers distinguish this species, which is leafless when flowering. There is one leaf on 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aguilar</emphasis>
34. It is 4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 cm, suborbicular, abruptly acute, basally cuneate, glabrous, abaxially white, strongly reticulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
